Bharat Petroleum Buys Brunei’s Champion Crude Oil From Astra

-- B y   P r a t i s h   N a r a y a n a n
-- 
2011-04-11T09:44:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-11/bharat-petroleum-buys-brunei-s-champion-crude-oil-from-astra.html
Bharat Petroleum Corp.,  India ’s
second-largest state-run oil refiner, bought about 600,000
barrels of  Brunei ’s Champion crude for loading in May from Astra
Oil Co., two people who participate in the market said.  The company had sought West African, North African, Caspian
or Asian low-sulfur crude cargoes of as much as 1 million
barrels each. The company, which typically purchases West
African crude, didn’t purchase those grades in the latest
tender, the people said.  Details of the purchase are as follows:  To contact the reporters on this story:
